&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt;&quot;&gt;As a Recruiting Specialist, you own the screening. Here&#39;s what the funnel looks like:&lt;br&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt;&quot;&gt;A short application with a couple of written questions → a practical take-home assessment → a 25-minute conversation → a final-round Super Day, consisting of two 1:1 conversations.&lt;br&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt;&quot;&gt;You&#39;ll review written applications, conduct the 25-minute structured conversations, and score candidates against a six-competency rubric, managing your own pipeline in Greenhouse and deciding who advances to the Super Day. The work is fast-paced, calibration-heavy, and requires someone who can hold a consistent bar across hundreds of conversations. Between waves, you&#39;ll help sharpen the rubric and the process so the next cohort&#39;s selection runs better than the last.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
